    "narrative": "For today\u2019s slate, **Tyler Freeman** (72.83) and **Will Smith** (71.28) anchor the lineup as our strongest plays, both benefiting from highly favorable conditions. **Tyler Freeman** draws a prime matchup against a pitcher with a ballooning 5.52 xERA and adds a massive +14% park factor boost, while **Will Smith** mirrors that environment, hitting in the heart of the order with a strong xwOBA profile. **Jos\u00e9 Ram\u00edrez** (66.01) remains a high-floor staple despite facing a tough arm in Rogers; his elite base projection keeps him in the starting core regardless of the opposing skill level. We are also seeing significant platoon-driven value today, particularly with **Jonathan Aranda** (63.33) and **Bryson Stott** (64.56), both of whom receive double-digit efficiency bumps for their right-handed handedness against opposing starters.\n\nThe most difficult bench decision involved **Matt Chapman** (52.74), who missed the cut despite a solid projection. While his park and order position offered moderate upside, he was ultimately squeezed out by the efficiency of **Luis Arraez** and **Gleyber Torres**, whose roles atop the order provide a more stable accumulation of counting stats in our 5x5 format. Risks remain on the horizon, specifically regarding **Gleyber Torres** and **Wenceel Perez**, who are both facing the elite arm of Crochet. While the park factors for **Gleyber Torres** and **Wenceel Perez** offer some buffer, their scores are dragged down by a -19% SP skill penalty, making them candidates for underperformance if they fail to capitalize on their platoon advantages early. Keep a close eye on the late-afternoon weather, as any delays could impact the consistency of our primary contributors.",
